<TITLE> Israeli family held hostage by gunmen in Mumbai </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MUMBAI, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - An Israeli family is being held hostage by gunmen in a Mumbai apartment building following a series of attacks in the city that have killed at least 86 people, police said. Local residents said a rabbi, his wife and two children live in and own the building, but it was not clear if they were the hostages. Gunfire could be heard from the area, a Reuters reporter on the scene said
